# Browser automation

Use **NPC MCP tools** (`npc_*`) to control the user's **Brave browser** via the NPC extension.

**Never** use `cursor-ide-browser` or built-in Browser Tab tools for browser tasks.

**Never** fall back to `curl`, `wget`, `fetch`, or any API call when NPC tools fail. If NPC is not connected, tell the user to click the NPC icon on a Brave tab and wait. Do NOT silently switch to an API workaround.

## Startup sequence

1. Call `npc_status` first to check connection
2. If `extensionConnected: false` or `sessionId: null`, tell the user to click the NPC icon on a tab
3. Only proceed with browser commands after `npc_status` shows a valid session

## Tool mapping

| Task | Use |
|------|-----|
| Check health | `npc_status` |
| Screenshot | `npc_screenshot` (optional `savePath` to save to disk) |
| Navigate | `npc_navigate` |
| Click | `npc_click` |
| Type | `npc_type` |
| Press key | `npc_press_key` |
| Scroll | `npc_scroll` |
| Find element | `npc_find` (CSS selector or text content) |
| Wait for element | `npc_wait_for` (polls until element appears) |
| Batch actions | `npc_batch` (array of actions in one call) |
| Read page text | `npc_extract_text` |
| Run JS | `npc_evaluate` |
| Current URL | `npc_current_url` |

## Performance

Prefer `npc_batch` for multi-step sequences (click + type + enter). One round-trip instead of three.

Prefer `npc_find` over screenshot-then-guess-coordinates. It returns center (x, y) ready for clicking.

Use `npc_wait_for` after navigation or SPA route changes instead of screenshot-retry loops.

## If tools fail

- Red `!` on NPC icon -> relay not running (`cd ~/Desktop/npc/npc-cli && npm run relay`)
- Gray icon -> click NPC icon on the tab you want to control
- Green `1` badge -> ready
- "Not connected" -> extension WS dropped, click NPC icon again
